Reformatted Question: Megan had <fact1>40 homework problems</fact1>. She finished <fact2>26 of them</fact2> but still had <fact3>2 pages</fact3> of problems to do. If <fact4>each page has the same number of problems on it</fact4>, how many problems are on each page?

Answer: Megan started with <fact1>40 problems</fact1> and finished <fact2>26</fact2>, leaving 40−26=14 problems. These remaining problems are spread across <fact3>2 pages equally</fact3>, as stated by <fact4>, so each page must have 14/<fact3>2</fact3>=7 problems. The answer is {7}.

question: Wendy picked 103 flowers for her friend’s wedding. She was making bouquets with 8 flowers in each one. If 47 of the flowers wilted before the wedding, how many bouquets could she still make?

Answer: Wendy started with <fact1>103 flowers</fact1>, but <fact3>47 wilted</fact3>, leaving 103 - 47 = 56 flowers.  With <fact2>8 flowers per bouquet</fact2>, she can make 56 / <fact2>8</fact2> = 7 bouquets. The answer is {7}.

Reformatted Question: Roger had <fact1>120 pieces of clothing</fact1> to wash. He put <fact2>48 of them in one load</fact2>, but decided to split <fact3>the rest</fact3> into <fact4>9 equal loads</fact4>. How many pieces of clothing could go in each of the small loads?
Answer: Roger had <fact1>120 pieces</fact1> of clothing and washed <fact2>48</fact2> in one load. This means <fact3>the rest</fact3> is <fact1>120</fact1>−<fact2>48</fact2>=72 pieces.  He wants to split these 72 pieces into <fact4>9 equal loads</fact4>, so each load will have 72/<fact4>9</fact4>=8 pieces of clothing. The answer is {8}.

question: Wendy picked 45 flowers for her friend’s wedding. She was making bouquets with 5 flowers in each one. If 35 of the flowers wilted before the wedding, how many bouquets could she still make?
answer:
Reformatted Question: Wendy picked <fact1>45 flowers</fact1> for her friend’s wedding. She was making bouquets with <fact2>5 flowers in each one</fact2>. If <fact3>35 of the flowers wilted</fact3> before the wedding, how many bouquets could she still make?

Answer: Wendy began with <fact1>45 flowers</fact1>.  Since <fact3>35 wilted</fact3>, she had 45 - <fact3>35</fact3> = 10 flowers left.  With <fact2>5 flowers per bouquet</fact2>, she could make 10 / <fact2>5</fact2> = 2 bouquets. The answer is {2}.
